24:57.520 --> 24:59.520
how the whale got his throat

25:00.920 --> 25:03.220
the whale is a big animal

25:03.220 --> 25:04.840
and he lives in the sea

25:04.840 --> 25:07.260
he is always hungry and eats

25:07.260 --> 25:09.460
many different fish and sea animals

25:10.080 --> 25:11.420
he doesn't have a throat

25:11.980 --> 25:14.120
and this means he can eat very big things

25:14.120 --> 25:16.240
as well as very small things

25:17.100 --> 25:18.560
a very small fish

25:18.560 --> 25:19.940
called the little fish

25:20.320 --> 25:21.620
also lives in the sea

25:22.300 --> 25:23.280
he is clever

25:24.120 --> 25:27.600
the whale is eating all the fish in the sea

25:27.600 --> 25:29.120
the little fish thinks

25:29.120 --> 25:30.800
I'm afraid

25:31.520 --> 25:33.500
I don't want him to eat me

25:34.340 --> 25:36.760
I must hide behind his ear

25:37.560 --> 25:40.820
but suddenly the whale stands up on his big tail

25:40.820 --> 25:42.580
and sees the little fish

25:43.500 --> 25:44.860
I'm hungry

25:44.860 --> 25:47.580
says the whale in a loud voice

25:48.660 --> 25:49.680
what's this?

25:50.840 --> 25:51.980
a little fish

25:52.860 --> 25:54.420
hello great whale

25:54.420 --> 25:56.380
says the little fish

25:56.380 --> 25:58.800
do you like eating man?

25:59.440 --> 26:01.280
I don't know

26:01.740 --> 26:02.620
says the whale

26:02.620 --> 26:04.300
looking at the little fish

26:04.860 --> 26:07.940
I prefer dolphins or sharks

26:08.900 --> 26:11.060
what is man like?

26:11.060 --> 26:14.980
oh man is very good

26:14.980 --> 26:17.100
says the clever little fish

26:17.100 --> 26:18.200
really?

26:19.120 --> 26:20.180
says the whale

26:20.980 --> 26:21.320
yes

26:22.020 --> 26:23.000
says the little fish

26:23.000 --> 26:24.460
believe me

26:25.700 --> 26:28.120
can you find a man for me

26:28.120 --> 26:29.680
asks the whale

26:29.680 --> 26:32.080
of course I can

26:32.080 --> 26:33.640
says the little fish

26:34.380 --> 26:36.580
you must swim to the north

26:36.580 --> 26:38.860
and in the middle of the sea

26:38.860 --> 26:41.560
there is a young sailor on a raft

26:42.260 --> 26:44.440
he's wearing blue trousers

26:44.440 --> 26:45.740
and braces

26:47.020 --> 26:48.760
good let's go

26:48.760 --> 26:50.080
says the whale

26:50.860 --> 26:52.560
the whale and the little fish

26:52.560 --> 26:54.140
swim across the sea

26:54.800 --> 26:56.700
soon the whale sees the sailor

26:56.700 --> 26:57.720
sitting on a raft

26:59.660 --> 27:02.140
good I'm very hungry

27:02.820 --> 27:03.560
says the whale

27:03.560 --> 27:05.500
he opens his big mouth

27:05.500 --> 27:07.200
and eats the young sailor

27:07.200 --> 27:08.240
and the raft

27:10.900 --> 27:12.560
says the whale

27:12.560 --> 27:15.500
man is very good

27:15.500 --> 27:18.020
the sailor and his raft

27:18.020 --> 27:20.180
are inside the whale's stomach

27:20.180 --> 27:22.480
what's happening to me?

27:22.840 --> 27:23.700
thinks the sailor

27:24.240 --> 27:25.100
he is afraid

27:25.100 --> 27:27.000
where am I?

27:28.040 --> 27:30.100
it's warm and dark in here

27:30.820 --> 27:32.060
oh no

27:32.060 --> 27:34.020
I'm inside a whale

27:34.020 --> 27:36.120
what can I do?

27:36.920 --> 27:38.640
the sailor is very clever

27:38.640 --> 27:39.940
and looks around

27:39.940 --> 27:41.800
he starts thinking

27:41.800 --> 27:44.820
this whale can't eat me

27:44.820 --> 27:46.300
he says angrily

27:46.300 --> 27:48.340
he starts jumping

27:48.340 --> 27:50.080
kicking and dancing

27:50.080 --> 27:51.680
inside the whale's stomach

27:51.680 --> 27:54.060
the whale is very unhappy

27:54.060 --> 27:55.620
and feels ill

27:55.620 --> 27:59.720
I've got a terrible stomach ache

28:00.820 --> 28:02.660
says the unhappy whale

28:02.660 --> 28:04.920
I'm sorry whale

28:04.920 --> 28:06.540
says the little fish

28:07.400 --> 28:09.660
what's the sailor doing?

28:10.380 --> 28:11.300
asks the whale

28:11.300 --> 28:14.560
do you know little fish?

28:15.440 --> 28:16.920
I don't know

28:16.920 --> 28:18.240
says the little fish

28:18.240 --> 28:20.400
the sailor continues

28:20.400 --> 28:22.560
jumping kicking and dancing

28:22.560 --> 28:23.980
inside the whale's stomach

28:23.980 --> 28:25.800
oh says the whale

28:26.450 --> 28:27.720
I feel sick

28:28.650 --> 28:30.360
I'm going to ask the sailor

28:30.360 --> 28:31.280
to come out

28:31.280 --> 28:32.740
says the little fish

28:33.360 --> 28:34.640
thank you

28:35.280 --> 28:36.560
that's a good idea

28:37.200 --> 28:38.020
says the whale

28:38.860 --> 28:40.820
please come out

28:41.360 --> 28:42.580
cries the little fish

28:43.360 --> 28:44.160
what?

28:45.300 --> 28:46.080
answers the sailor

28:46.080 --> 28:50.440
the whale's got a terrible stomach ache

28:50.440 --> 28:51.700
says the little fish

28:52.360 --> 28:54.680
please come out right now

28:55.360 --> 28:58.180
no I'm not coming out

28:58.180 --> 29:00.200
says the sailor angrily

29:00.200 --> 29:03.760
you must take me home to England first

29:03.760 --> 29:05.560
all right

29:07.020 --> 29:08.500
says the poor whale

29:09.400 --> 29:11.480
I can take you home

29:12.640 --> 29:14.560
the whale and the little fish

29:14.560 --> 29:16.040
start swimming fast

29:16.040 --> 29:18.400
they swim across the sea to England

29:18.400 --> 29:21.220
while the whale and the little fish swim

29:21.220 --> 29:23.320
the sailor breaks up the raft

29:23.320 --> 29:25.280
and ties the pieces together

29:25.280 --> 29:26.040
with his braces

29:26.040 --> 29:28.840
when they get to the beach in England

29:28.840 --> 29:31.620
the sailor has a big surprise

29:31.620 --> 29:32.500
for the whale

29:34.080 --> 29:36.800
whale open your big mouth

29:36.800 --> 29:38.600
says the sailor

29:38.600 --> 29:40.480
I want to get out

29:41.420 --> 29:43.440
the whale opens his mouth

29:43.440 --> 29:45.420
and the sailor walks out

29:45.420 --> 29:48.760
but he leaves his raft in the whale's mouth

29:48.760 --> 29:52.360
now my raft is your throat

29:52.360 --> 29:55.280
and you can never eat men again

29:55.280 --> 29:56.560
says the sailor

29:56.910 --> 29:57.960
with this raft

29:57.960 --> 30:00.900
you can only eat very small fish

30:00.900 --> 30:02.160
what?

30:02.840 --> 30:05.280
only very small fish

30:06.190 --> 30:07.720
says the whale angrily

30:08.010 --> 30:10.700
I don't want this in my throat

30:10.700 --> 30:16.700
the whale coughs and coughs

30:16.700 --> 30:18.400
but the raft doesn't move

30:18.950 --> 30:22.320
he is very sad and slowly swims away

30:22.320 --> 30:24.360
the sailor is on the beach

30:24.360 --> 30:26.380
and watches the whale swim away

30:27.320 --> 30:28.680
goodbye whale

30:28.680 --> 30:30.440
says the sailor happily

30:30.440 --> 30:32.760
now you can't eat men anymore

30:34.620 --> 30:36.360
men aren't nice

30:36.360 --> 30:39.120
and they give me a stomach ache

30:39.120 --> 30:40.100
says the whale

30:40.860 --> 30:44.020
small fish are much better

30:48.180 --> 30:48.860
whales

30:50.120 --> 30:52.180
what do you know about whales?

30:53.300 --> 30:54.760
here are some interesting facts

30:55.940 --> 30:57.580
whales live in the sea

30:57.580 --> 30:59.040
but they are not fish

30:59.040 --> 31:00.100
they are mammals

31:00.100 --> 31:02.200
they need air to live

31:02.200 --> 31:05.020
they must come up to the top of the water

31:05.020 --> 31:05.460
often

31:05.460 --> 31:06.660
to get air

31:06.660 --> 31:09.360
they breathe air in and out

31:09.360 --> 31:11.500
through the blowhole on their back

31:12.120 --> 31:13.680
when whales sleep

31:13.680 --> 31:15.840
they stay on the top of the water

31:15.840 --> 31:19.540
the biggest whale is the blue whale

31:19.540 --> 31:21.980
it is around 30 meters long

31:21.980 --> 31:24.320
and weighs about 200 tons

31:25.840 --> 31:29.520
whales swim by moving their tails up and down

31:29.520 --> 31:31.280
and by using their flippers

31:31.840 --> 31:34.680
their flippers help them to turn around

31:34.680 --> 31:37.240
whales make a lot of noise

31:37.240 --> 31:39.300
because they talk to each other

31:39.840 --> 31:43.460
their underwater sounds can travel very far

31:45.840 --> 31:47.700
whales usually live in groups

31:47.700 --> 31:50.960
a baby whale is called a calf

31:51.840 --> 31:53.840
plural, calves

31:55.760 --> 31:58.800
whales move from one place to another

31:58.800 --> 32:01.040
during the warm summer months

32:01.040 --> 32:04.020
they eat a lot because they get ready for the

32:04.020 --> 32:04.300
winter

32:04.840 --> 32:07.680
in the autumn they start moving south

32:07.680 --> 32:08.960
to warm places

32:08.960 --> 32:11.940
and in the spring they move north

32:12.650 --> 32:17.220
the killer whale is a very popular and dangerous whale

32:17.220 --> 32:19.540
here is some information about it

32:19.540 --> 32:21.960
the killer whale

32:21.960 --> 32:23.660
name

32:23.660 --> 32:25.140
orca

32:25.140 --> 32:26.900
or killer whale

32:26.900 --> 32:28.460
color

32:28.460 --> 32:29.780
black

32:29.780 --> 32:30.560
and white

32:30.560 --> 32:32.140
size

32:32.140 --> 32:35.060
around 8 meters for males

32:35.060 --> 32:37.000
and 7 meters for females

32:38.120 --> 32:39.020
lives

32:39.020 --> 32:41.160
in all major oceans

32:41.160 --> 32:45.640
from the Arctic areas of Alaska, Canada, Scandinavia

32:45.640 --> 32:48.460
and Russia to the warm oceans in the south

32:49.160 --> 32:52.540
they usually live in groups of around 40 whales

32:53.320 --> 32:57.200
the killer whale can live for 30 to 50 years

32:58.860 --> 33:01.540
eats, fish and other sea animals

33:02.040 --> 33:04.060
a very dangerous predator

33:08.140 --> 33:10.380
how the camel got his hump

33:11.300 --> 33:15.080
the horse, the dog and the ox work for the

33:15.080 --> 33:15.380
farmer

33:15.380 --> 33:17.320
but the camel does not

33:17.320 --> 33:20.700
he has a long neck and long legs

33:21.360 --> 33:23.240
he lives alone in the desert

33:23.240 --> 33:25.140
and doesn't want to work

33:25.140 --> 33:27.340
he eats and sleeps

33:27.340 --> 33:30.020
and when someone speaks to him

33:30.020 --> 33:30.780
he says

33:30.780 --> 33:31.660
hump

33:31.660 --> 33:36.380
on Monday morning the horse goes to see the camel

33:36.380 --> 33:38.700
camel says the horse

33:38.700 --> 33:41.360
come and work like all the other animals

33:41.360 --> 33:44.680
I carry men on my back and work hard all

33:44.680 --> 33:45.020
day

33:45.020 --> 33:45.720
hump

33:46.500 --> 33:49.400
says the camel and the horse goes away

33:50.300 --> 33:53.780
on Tuesday morning the dog goes to see the camel

33:53.780 --> 33:56.140
camel says the dog

33:56.140 --> 33:58.360
come and work like all the other animals

33:58.360 --> 34:00.740
I guard the farmer's house

34:01.200 --> 34:03.660
I work hard day and night

34:03.660 --> 34:06.180
hump says the camel

34:06.180 --> 34:08.160
and the dog goes away

34:09.180 --> 34:12.980
on Wednesday the big ox goes to see the camel

34:12.980 --> 34:15.940
camel says the big ox

34:15.940 --> 34:17.760
come and work for the farmer

34:18.360 --> 34:20.580
I work hard in the country all day

34:21.840 --> 34:23.700
hump says the camel

34:24.160 --> 34:25.800
and the ox goes away

34:26.840 --> 34:30.120
the animals go and tell the farmer about the lazy

34:30.120 --> 34:30.520
camel

34:30.520 --> 34:33.240
the camel is very lazy

34:33.560 --> 34:34.360
says the horse

34:34.360 --> 34:36.000
he doesn't want to work

34:36.580 --> 34:37.380
says the ox

34:37.380 --> 34:39.720
he just eats and sleeps

34:39.720 --> 34:40.660
and says

34:40.660 --> 34:43.220
hump says the dog

34:43.800 --> 34:46.600
the farmer thinks for a moment and then says

34:46.600 --> 34:49.260
you three must work more than

34:49.720 --> 34:50.060
what?

34:50.820 --> 34:51.900
the animals say

34:51.900 --> 34:54.060
but we don't want to work more

34:54.060 --> 34:58.580
you must work more because the camel doesn't want to

34:58.580 --> 34:58.940
work

34:58.940 --> 35:00.500
says the farmer

35:01.060 --> 35:05.040
the horse the ox and the dog are very angry

35:05.040 --> 35:06.540
and they start talking

35:07.300 --> 35:09.980
the camel walks by and listens to them

35:09.980 --> 35:13.200
hump says the camel

35:13.200 --> 35:15.000
and goes away laughing

35:15.960 --> 35:18.380
the animals don't know what to do

35:18.380 --> 35:19.700
we need help

35:19.700 --> 35:20.800
says the horse

35:20.800 --> 35:24.140
yes says the dog sadly

35:24.140 --> 35:26.300
but who can help us?

35:27.160 --> 35:31.000
suddenly the desert magician arrives on a big cloud

35:31.800 --> 35:34.620
he is a great magician and lives in the desert

35:34.620 --> 35:37.160
he is everyone's friend

35:37.800 --> 35:38.160
hello?

35:38.840 --> 35:39.280
he says

35:39.790 --> 35:41.260
what are you talking about?

35:42.120 --> 35:43.060
why are you angry?

35:43.940 --> 35:45.280
oh desert magician

35:45.670 --> 35:46.500
says the horse

35:46.500 --> 35:48.300
we have a big problem

35:48.300 --> 35:50.140
what's your problem?

35:50.800 --> 35:52.000
asks the desert magician

35:52.000 --> 35:53.980
tell me about it

35:53.980 --> 35:57.740
the camel in the desert doesn't want to work

35:57.740 --> 35:58.880
says the horse

35:58.880 --> 36:01.680
why doesn't he want to work?

36:02.220 --> 36:03.960
asks the desert magician

36:03.960 --> 36:05.680
he is lazy

36:06.300 --> 36:07.120
says the ox

36:07.120 --> 36:08.080
yes

36:08.080 --> 36:09.540
says the horse

36:09.540 --> 36:10.980
very lazy

36:10.980 --> 36:13.780
and we must do more work

36:13.780 --> 36:15.000
says the dog

36:15.000 --> 36:18.300
we already work hard all day long

36:18.300 --> 36:19.460
says the ox

36:20.000 --> 36:22.300
what does the camel say?

36:22.840 --> 36:24.540
asks the desert magician

36:24.540 --> 36:26.580
he always says

36:26.580 --> 36:27.520
hump

36:27.520 --> 36:29.280
says the horse

36:29.980 --> 36:32.360
i must go and talk to the camel

36:33.000 --> 36:34.560
says the desert magician

36:35.480 --> 36:38.120
the desert magician's magic cloud

36:38.120 --> 36:39.560
carries him to the desert

36:39.560 --> 36:41.440
and he sees the camel

36:41.440 --> 36:44.380
he is standing near a pool of water

36:45.140 --> 36:47.840
why don't you want to work camel?

36:48.520 --> 36:50.080
asks the desert magician

36:50.980 --> 36:51.700
humph

36:52.500 --> 36:53.620
says the camel

36:53.620 --> 36:55.860
looking at the pool of water

36:55.860 --> 36:58.960
the other animals must work more

36:58.960 --> 37:01.320
because you don't work

37:01.320 --> 37:03.260
says the desert magician

37:04.080 --> 37:04.800
humph

37:04.800 --> 37:06.380
says the camel

37:07.200 --> 37:08.380
don't say

37:09.200 --> 37:09.920
humph

37:09.920 --> 37:11.500
says the desert magician

37:11.500 --> 37:14.300
you must start working

37:14.300 --> 37:17.160
the camel looks at himself

37:17.160 --> 37:18.640
in the pool of water

37:18.640 --> 37:21.980
i'm a great magician

37:21.980 --> 37:23.860
thinks the desert magician

37:23.860 --> 37:26.600
what magic can i do?

37:27.560 --> 37:30.260
the camel must work

37:30.920 --> 37:33.520
the desert magician sits down

37:33.520 --> 37:35.500
and thinks about something magic

37:35.500 --> 37:38.640
suddenly the camel has a big

37:38.640 --> 37:40.100
hump on his back

37:40.700 --> 37:42.580
he looks in the pool of water

37:42.580 --> 37:43.260
and sees it

37:43.260 --> 37:45.160
he is very surprised

37:46.200 --> 37:47.620
what's that on my back?

37:48.320 --> 37:49.980
he asks the desert magician

37:50.800 --> 37:51.580
it's your

37:52.440 --> 37:53.000
humph

37:53.640 --> 37:55.100
says the desert magician

37:55.940 --> 37:57.360
i don't like it

37:57.360 --> 37:58.840
and i don't want it

37:58.840 --> 38:00.140
says the camel

38:00.140 --> 38:00.980
angrily

38:01.880 --> 38:03.560
how can i work with this

38:03.560 --> 38:04.780
hump on my back

38:04.780 --> 38:07.320
now you can work more

38:07.320 --> 38:08.560
than the other animals

38:08.560 --> 38:10.400
says the desert magician

38:10.400 --> 38:11.960
with your hump

38:11.960 --> 38:14.840
you don't need to eat or drink

38:14.840 --> 38:16.360
for three days

38:16.360 --> 38:17.200
what?

38:17.900 --> 38:19.140
says the camel angrily

38:19.780 --> 38:21.740
i don't want to work

38:21.740 --> 38:24.280
now be quiet

38:24.280 --> 38:27.100
and start working

38:27.100 --> 38:29.580
says the desert magician

38:29.580 --> 38:32.720
the camel walks away slowly

38:32.720 --> 38:34.680
and joins the other animals

38:35.720 --> 38:37.560
when the other animals see him

38:37.560 --> 38:39.960
they laugh and laugh

38:40.720 --> 38:42.200
on that day

38:42.200 --> 38:44.100
the camel starts working

38:44.560 --> 38:46.920
but he still isn't friendly

